I have been to Britain, and farming is not a big business so their competence would primarily be as truck farmers, that is small scale vegetable gardens.  So I consider them competent at what they do but not as compared to the world wide universe of farmers.

I did not care about the nationalities, it was the job or title given that mattered to me.  An inmate is not competent or caring or they would never have committed the crime.  A lawyer might be very competent, but I don't always think they are caring or warm.

I intentionally answered the way I did, because I don't think enough information was provided about the people to accurately judge them on either category provided to me. For example, people are frequently sent to prison for crimes they didn't commit. People also hold jobs that they aren't necessarily very good at. Thus, I would need more information to accurately assess people.
